      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely understandable why this feels unsettling, as it touches upon the deepest aspects of personal privacy. The targeting is not random; it is a highly sophisticated form of personalization that drives their business models. By understanding your emotional state, they can tailor experiences—like lighting or temperature—to keep you engaged with their ecosystem, which is the ultimate goal of their service. This level of intimate data collection is precisely what makes these systems so powerful and, frankly, so deeply invasive.",
